'''Kip Edwards''' (born December 4, 1989) is an [[American football]] [[cornerback]] for the [[Saskatchewan Roughriders]] of the [[Canadian Football League]] (CFL). He was signed by the [[Buffalo Bills]] as an [[undrafted free agent]] in 2013. He played [[college football]] at [[Missouri Tigers football|Missouri]].

Edwards has also been a member of the [[Buffalo Bills]] and [[Minnesota Vikings]].

==Professional career==

===Buffalo Bills===
Edwards was signed by the Bills after going undrafted in the [[2013 NFL Draft]]. He attended training camp and played in four preseason games and was released shortly after.

===Cleveland Browns===
He was signed by the Browns after being cut by the Bills in 2013. He was later released.

===Minnesota Vikings===
He was signed by the Vikings and was placed on the practice squad<ref>http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/players/playerpage/1630773/kip-edwards</ref> after being released by the Bills. He was waived by the Vikings in June 2014.<ref>http://www.vikings.com/team/transactions.html</ref>

